1
00:00:03,665 --> 00:00:06,287
[SPEAKER_02]: just from a young age, I really enjoyed building things.

2
00:00:10,330 --> 00:00:29,183
[SPEAKER_02]: I wanna teach my skills because I feel like younger people can benefit from learning how to work with their hands, learning how to work with others, and to me, I just get a great deal of satisfaction from helping to train the workforce.

3
00:00:30,064 --> 00:00:36,786
[SPEAKER_04]: Basically what we do in carpentry, it's mainly working with wood, so just building stuff.

4
00:00:41,622 --> 00:00:44,463
[SPEAKER_00]: I would love for every student to go into carpentry.

5
00:00:44,623 --> 00:00:50,604
[SPEAKER_00]: Maybe someday have their own business, which I was fortunate enough to still have almost 40 years now.

6
00:00:50,624 --> 00:00:59,547
[SPEAKER_00]: I find it to be very self-rewarding to be able to run your own business and accomplish jobs start to finish.

7
00:01:01,467 --> 00:01:04,650
[SPEAKER_04]: I was really interested in it during my rotations.

8
00:01:04,750 --> 00:01:14,720
[SPEAKER_04]: The teachers especially, Mr. Lumino, Mr. Marciano were always super nice, super funny to me and just made the shop overall just really welcoming.

9
00:01:15,341 --> 00:01:21,187
[SPEAKER_03]: I chose this shop because I felt like that it was the most hands-on shop and I thought that it would be the most fun.

10
00:01:22,461 --> 00:01:26,623
[SPEAKER_01]: I choose this shop because Cambridge gives you a lot of opportunities out there.

11
00:01:26,643 --> 00:01:33,726
[SPEAKER_01]: It makes you feel like part of the team and also you get good money out of it.

12
00:01:34,406 --> 00:01:38,428
[SPEAKER_04]: Someone else should choose this shop because it's a good environment to go to at the end of the day.

13
00:01:38,768 --> 00:01:41,629
[SPEAKER_04]: If you have some stuff on your mind you get to let it off by building some stuff.

14
00:01:41,849 --> 00:01:47,471
[SPEAKER_03]: I think that the most valuable thing that I've learned here is probably teamwork and how to work well with others.

15
00:01:47,631 --> 00:01:48,352
[SPEAKER_03]: Teamwork.

16
00:01:48,472 --> 00:01:48,932
[SPEAKER_03]: Teamwork.

17
00:01:55,777 --> 00:02:00,238
[SPEAKER_02]: The great thing about carpentry is that at the end of the day, you have very tangible results.

18
00:02:00,919 --> 00:02:02,739
[SPEAKER_00]: I consider Rashtrap like a big family.

19
00:02:02,899 --> 00:02:03,699
[SPEAKER_00]: We're very close.

20
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:12,322
[SPEAKER_00]: We all get along well and we try to teach them what it's like to build as a team, to accomplish everything you can together.

21
00:02:12,362 --> 00:02:15,003
[SPEAKER_00]: There's not a lot you can get done in this world all by yourself.

